	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok fellas---I need some thoughts about a offer that I was presented with.&nbsp;&nbsp;I suppose that this is more directed to the higher level SKs, but anyone that has any thoughts, please let me know.<br><br>In exchange for my RBG (Waist item, AC7, STR+8, STA+8, DEX+8, HP+25, MANA+25, Haste27%, probably sells for about 30K on the server that I play on) I have been offered the following items:<br><br>Shard of Night, 1HP, 21 dmg, 24 dly, STR+5, INT+5, poison &amp; disease resist+5, Mana+25, SK only<br>(who KNOWS what on earth this goes for, as so few of them are ever sold on my server...)<br><br>AND<br><br>Atramentous Shield, AC28, STR+5, STA+5, INT+5, Magic resist+10, Cold &amp; fire resist+5, HP+50, Mana+50, SK ONLY (again--who knows the PC on my server....)<br><br>Note that both items are SK only, which means perhaps some difficulty selling these items in the future when I finally get one of the UBER weapon / shield drops from ToV (Sledge of Smashing anyone???  =)   )<br><br>Current weapons that I can wield are Strength of Grodan (41dmg, 51dly, STR+25, STA+10), Di'zok Imperial Katana (35dmg, 43 dly, plus a few buffs), Sword of Pain (19dmg, 25 dly, plus buffs), Ebon Mace (19dmg, 24 dly).  The current shield I use is a Sarnak Battle Shield.<br><br>Furthermore, I have a waist item (from moon--cant remember damn name cuz I dont wear it) ac20, STR+15, WIS+15 that I can wear if I sold RBG &amp; also have a Hangman's Noose as fallback haste item (AC5, 17% haste, can be worn on waist or head).  Granted, I can probably get a 24% haste item easy enough, perhaps even part of the deal (I think its the Dragonborn Sash--drops in HS if memory serves.  Again, not a need to memorize as I have had RBG with me for so long....hehe)<br><br>1HS, 2HS &amp; 1HB are all maxed out atm.  2HB is good, but not maxed.  Piercing SUCKS &amp; I would both have to dump some training points into it &amp; train like mad to get it to a decent level.<br><br>So, the question is--would you make the trade????<br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
