	   <tr><td colspan=2>SHHH, there are about 4 of the regular posters on this board who wil disagree with you about how much i know right now.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mostly it's just different experiences, but I'm glad thgis isn't a pvp environment (jk).<br><br>Right now I have 2 primary Weapons, but all skills are maxed.  I use 1hb (Ebon Mace and Sarnak Battle Shield) when Tanking of when in an AE environment.  I also use 2hs (either Strenght of Grodan or the Di`Zok Imperial Katana) when doing the secondary Melee Role.  You will do more damge with 2 handers but you can keep better agro and stay alive longer using a 1 hander and a shield.  I also keep a Dark Spear of Venom (no drop from Kael 17/27 procs sicken) for areas where I needed to keep alot of agro, but this is no longer as good as it was for that.  The Deathbringer Rod is still in my inventory to keep 2hb maxed and I use a Centi Short Sword as a cheap 1hs trainer as I have never had a good 1hs.<br><br>Best skill, hmmm, that I can FD 5 out of 6 times successfully :).  I always keep 1hb as my primary weapon skill, as the Bash and AC/resists from a shield make it essential in raids.  Once I got into the 50's i got some truely nice 2hs weapons and with the change in damage bonuses I found that there are situaltional reasons to use the better damage, lower taunt weapons.  I aslo use the Sash of the Dragonborne or the dropped Haste belt from Plane of Sky and Haste helps alot with the 2hs weapons I have.  <br><br>I think it's best to try and keep all your skills within about 50 points of max, then use the best weaonp you have at the time.  I never had any skill in piercing till level 35 when we raided Crystal caverns for the first time and I won roll on the Stallage Terrorspine Spear, then I maxed that skill as it was the best weaonp I had at the time.  I learned 2hb when I got a Rod of Lamidation at lvl 48.  I learned 2hb partnered with a Druid in Ocean of Tears at Seafury Cyclops.  We could kill non-stop (even with my poor weapons skills), got great xp and loot and I maxed my 2hb by the end of lvl 49, the pet even did well against these guys (imagine that).  At your level I'd suggest you find some low blue (even light blue) Giants to solo, or get into a group as the secondary tank and just keep swinging away with the 2hb.<br><br>But good luck.  Oh yeh and how far south is the &quot;Deep South&quot;, since I lived for 3 years in South Carolina, are you south of that?<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 60 DE Gravelord</td></tr>
