	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, May 13th 9:48 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.15]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You have a couple of options.<br><br>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;You can do a quest in Grobb to raise your faction with the Shadowknights there:  turn in bone chips, 4 at a time, to the guildmaster.<br><br>But this will hurt your faction back home with the Greenblood Shadowknights in Oggok.  <br><br>Making yourself acceptable in Grobb shouldn't lose you too much faction in Oggok.  If you find you're slipping down toward indifferent, you can always rebuild your Greenblood faction with one of the quests there.<br><br>2.  You can decide that that's too much trouble.  From most places in Innothule it will take you five minutes longer to get to Oggok than it will to get to Grobb.  Let's say you run home to train every time you ding, for 6 levels:  that's an extra 30 minutes spent on travel time.  Frankly I expect you'll spend much more than 30 minutes collecting enough bone chips to build faction in Grobb.  So it might be easier just to shrug and jog home to Oggok.<br><br> <br>&nbsp;<br>Macnair (le Grand Mac)<br>Shaman 60<br></td></tr>
