	   <a name=10201634081055></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10201634081055><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=10201634081055>RE: discipline's</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=10201634081055#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61489><span id=Scholar>Kamlatir, Eater of Souls</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>66 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 30th 6:50 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The only discipline I use is Unholy Aura, ever. As has been stated, fearless is next to useless on account of it's short duration. One could imagine it being good for those chance encounters in a new dungeon or zone where you suddenly get a mob you've never seen before and it fears. Sadly, once you realize you could've used this disc you are usually already feared. Resistant is actually a decent disc at the level you receive it and it enables you to go on single mob fights with the higher level persons in your guild, it does nothing for prolonged fighting in a caster heavy zone though, also due to it's short duration. Unholy aura works everywhere most of the time, a good call is to test casting a Torrent of Hate on the mob you're looking to blast. Torrent of Hate seems to be designed to increase the want for shadowknights in groups, it's very low aggro and isn't mr based. I've gotten the impression it's disease based but I haven't done any conclusive tests to this yet. It sticks on mobs that are 100 percent mr though. Leech Curse is the biggest disappointment yet for me in terms of the high level game for shadowknights. For 12 seconds you get healed for everything you hit a mob for. VI even remade it since sk's were complaining that most of the time they had disc sessions with half misses and half hits so they changed it so that you get an increased chance to hit when the disc is active. It doesn't change the fact that it's useless. Max hasted the damage you dish out in 12 seconds doesn't even begin to compare to the damage a warrior avoids using his defensive disc. If your idea of a 60 disc is to be able to tank a green mob for 12 seconds without needing a heal then Leech Curse is the disc for you. As for using it to establish aggro at the start of a fight, that's a warrior thing. They need time to get some hate from a mob, sk's don't. We have taunt spells and standing there tanking a mob to get aggro while the others are watching you is a complete waste of damage.<br><br>This is to be honest one of my biggest pet peaves about shadowknights as a class, the fact that their discs and aa abilities are somewhat lagging other classes in usefulness. By the time you get unholy aura HT has lost it's effectivness to quickly dispatch a mob and once used you have eliminated your chance to use both discs and HT for a long time. Other classes have discs that refresh in 10 or 15 minutes making them a tool you can weigh into strategies against different mobs, sk's can do something every 90 minutes and what they do most of the times has no effect what so ever. Many of the aa abilities are based on the HT timer, indeed some of them are a variant on HT. You have Super Harm Touch which is supposed to make your HT nearly unresistable. That was the thought with changing Unholy Aura to disease resist too and we know where that ended...You have Leech Touch, a harm touch that heals you the equivalent of the damage you do. Also works off of the HT timer and it can't be used with Unholy Aura so it's basically a heal for 800 or whatever your HT does when it's not enhanced by Unholy Aura. Both work of the HT timer, both take 90 minutes to refresh...So imagine yourself using Unholy Aura and blasting a mob with your HT. I then can't use another disc for 60 minutes and I can't use HT or any of the aa abilites on the HT timer for as long as that takes to refresh (think it's 72 minutes). Honestly, if they removed all discs but Unholy Aura and the aa abilities on the HT timer I'd be just as happy as I am today.<br><br>Kamlatir<br>Grave Lord of Far Seekers, The Rathe<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
