	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok I'd just like to clerify what I meant by using Lechcurse to establish agro.<br><br>Basically when a Raid goes bad and for some reason the Main Tank dies, usually there is a time when Clerics can't Complete Heal the new Main Tank because the Clerics have more agro than the Warrior.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have seen on several occations level 60 SK's pull agro then use this discipline to give them time to get more agro than the Clerics so healing can continue as normal.  Pali's can do the same thing using Lay Hands, but the real issue is to get someone with high agro who can withstand a beating for long enough to drop the Clerics down on the Hate list.  Warriors in Defensive Discipline generate so little agro that they can't do this.  I have seen a few Warriors establish themselves using their Auto-Rippost Discipline but that is not what most think to do when things go bad.<br><br>The most dangerous time during a Raid is just after a Main Tank dies.  The normal result is many dead Clerics and then the rest of the Raid running for their lives while Warriors give them time to gate or camp out.  When an SK or Pali is present and immediately grabs agro AND avoids needing a heal for about 10 seconds the Raid can normally recover.<br><br>That's just my take on how I've seen that discipline use effectively.  Other people may have other techniques to recover on a raid gone bad, but I have seen this one work many times.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant<br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 60 DE Gravelord</td></tr>
