	   <tr><td colspan=2>While you get each discipline at the designated level:<br>Resistant at lvl 51<br>Fearless at lvl 52 (?)<br>Unholly Aura at lvl 55<br>Leechcurse at lvl 60<br><br>some are useful, some are not.&nbsp;&nbsp;For example Feraless is almost completely useless, a 15 second fear immunity is not of value in fighting Dragons.  While Resistant is extremely benefitial when fighting AE MOBs, extra resistances is never a waste (+10 to all saves).<br><br>Unholy Aura is a double edged sword, sometimes it helps, sometimes it results in comlete resists.  Always check disease resistance before trying this on a MOB, it not only adds about 50 extra damage to your HT it also makes it Disease based for resistance checks.  On some magic resistant MOBs this has allowed me to do the best dd of anyone in the group, other times when a MOB needed to be turned this has given complete resists, making for a bad day :(.  A note that Shaman Slow spells are disease based, if a MOB can be slowed then you can use Discipline with HT on them generally.<br><br>Leechcurse when active will heal you equal to ever point of melee damage you do to a MOB.  I've seen it used to great effect when trying to grab initial agro on a MOB when playing Main Tank Role.  It's fairly short duration though so it must be kept in perspective.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Apr 29 08:56:36 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 60 DE Gravelord</td></tr>
