	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.15]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>i want point out that i agree much with what neptunis and lunatic said about group contribution. by talking about aggro i was not implying that it is ALL you add to a group, just that it is an immediate thing that you can work on that will really help your group out.<br><br>another thing i thought to mention is at lvl 9 there is now a debuff spell (wasn't when i started out) , and at lvl 15 another buff / debuff spell - despair / scream of hate. you can definately help out your group by casting both of these on mobs. they lower their attk when stacked by 13 which is significant i think.<br><br>remember also that darkness is both a dot and a slower. makes it harder for groups to run and cauese damage - so lvl 15 clinging darkness can benefit a group quite a bit too.<br><br>lastly, although you can't eat damage like a warrior (you'll never be able too), remember that you eat it a lot better than rogues, healers, nukers. so keep it in perspective. it's better you are getting beat on than them. sure you're no warrior but you're not a total slouch on hp either. if the aggro is on the warrior in the group - focus on dealing damage and debuffing, but don't taunt or cast disease as this is likely to get it on you. however, if the aggro is on that rogue who's trying to backstab, or that cleric that keeps you alive - taunt like a mother%$^&amp;* and hit that disease gem. bash helps too.<br><br>i also agree with lunatic about self-sufficiency. when you hit 30. you will suddenly feel much more sufficient in both a solo and group role. you'll be able to invis and explore ahead in many dungeons for example. and be able to cancel bad pulls to your group by FD'ing (keep that abjuration up and remember you MUST turn attack OFF for FD to work (thanx again lunatic on that one) ). best way to do this i think is make a hot key<br><br>/attack off<br>/cast 8<br><br>this assumes FD is in 8 slot of course.<br><br>and lifetaps DO save healers mana. if you find yourself in a situation where you are not ALWAYS the one with aggro you should be able to keep your health up fairly well using your lifetaps.<br><br>when soloing when the mob starts to run you can also stop attacking and lifetap the target to death - this way you have MUCH less downtime waiting for your health back.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
