	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well &quot;just die&quot; when you have an option not to is just not reasonable.<br><br>On a Raid your &quot;just die&quot; may cost 20 minutes to an hour of the parties time to get you back, rezzed and ready to try the pull again.&nbsp;&nbsp;Often times you FD when you have extra agro you need to dump away from a group, so are you going to run to an remote corner of Sebelis and die on a bad pull?  If so how do you expect to get your corpse back?  And when the Raid gets slaughtered, who pulls the corpses to the save spot for rezzing?  The SK's and Monks who have FD and are still in zone.<br><br>FD is a tremendous tool we have, to not use it is stupid.  And it works alot more often then 50/50, it's about 80% effective at my level and if you FD soon enough you may get another try anyway upping the chances it will save your life.  Ask most melee classes which of our abilities they would like to have and it will be FD, they've seen it save our lives too often.<br><br>FD is your best friend, learn it, practice it, rely on it.  To encourage anyone to not use it is irresponsible.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant<br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 60 DE Gravelord</td></tr>
