	   <a name=102070768787387></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102070768787387><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102070768787387>RE: FD</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=102070768787387#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=159157><span id= >MNParadox</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>9 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, May 6th 1:54 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a 35 DE SK.&nbsp;&nbsp;I've been playing mainly in lower guk for the last few levels.  FD is a godsend!  I tell you, set up a macro to cast endure cold and max Abjuration out ASAP!  FD goes off the same spell skill.  FD pulling is one of the best things in the world.  Make sure you're buffed from the casters in the group - SOW helps this a lot.  Go up to a group, let them all aggro on you - don't even hit the attack button, just walk into the middle of them.  Run a bit from the spawn area with the train behind you.  Hit the FD macro, and if successful, flip to alternate views to watch the mobs leave.  As soon as you have a manageable number of mobs still near you, get back up and let them aggro on you again and haul them back to the group to slaughter.  Then, go back and get the rest!<br><br>I've also used FD to not only save my own butt, but the butts of the group as well.  There are a few times when I am main tank... mainly because the people who I group with have come to know me well.  But there are still times when I am not &quot;Alpha Tank&quot; but take the role of &quot;Beta Tank&quot;.  A few times, my group has been over pulled and the MT died or was about to die - for some reason, I just couldn't take the aggro away - oh, well, that happens.  The group is getting ready to flee and, of course, the mobs attack the cleric.  I've run up, dotted them and did the area effect debuff.  BAM!  All are on me now.  The cleric backs off and becomes safe.  I tell the group to zone and they take off.  Now, at this time, I've got a good number of mobs on me that love the taste of my blue skin.  Once the rest of the group is safe, I'll turn off attack and start jamming on the FD macro.  The other day, I managed to save the group and myself with under 30 hps left. - all because of FD.  Everyone lived.  We were all hurting bad, but no exp loss.<br><br>Now, I'm not going to lie.  There are times, that FD hasn't worked when I needed it most.  But that's the way things go.  It's happened when I've done the tactic in the paragraph above.  However, I've been able to get the cleric out so she could come back in and rez.  Twice now, she has donated for me to get a rez higher than what she could give me - all because I was able to let her get out.<br><br>SKs are underrated at times.  We are aggro - it's in our blood and the mobs love to get their fill.  We can also deal out some damn nice damage - and take a good deal of it as well.  Sure, at times, it's not as high as a warrior, but when it comes to crowd control and killing that crowd... an SK, ENCH, CLER, BARD/NECRO, WAR, ROG/BST group can walk through some nasty places.<br><br>People play different styles - that's totally cool.  But having FD as an SK skill... it is completely worth having it and being able to use it well.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
