	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay since my favorite alt is an SK, i thought i'd say something here about how i view his pet from admitadly a life long druids perspective.<br><br>The SK pet is a VERY mana efficient DoT spell and root spell. There you have it. He serves two real purposes. Mainly while soloing, but also useful at times while grouping. <br><br>He's like my DS spell, a DoT spell, or a monks damage. most don't realize the tremendous damage those spells do, because like the monk, it's a little damage alot of times over a battle.<br><br>Personally i love the little skinny bastard. Not playing a class with SoW anymore, he has faithfully died (again i suppose, since he was undead in the first place) to give me running time more times then i can remember.<br><br>Stacked on top of the Harm Touch, and Fear spells, and Clinging Darkness line, he's the reason i play my SK as my only melee alt (i have a ranger too, but the comparison of who can solo better at level 20 is insane, the SK could take 4 mobs in the time it takes the ranger to take one, unless it's a animal)<br><br>Now if only i can convince Verant to give my main a skeleton... beat the hell out of that freaky bear i get.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
